cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.RO

The paper presents a deep learning approach to compensate for power fluctuations in photovoltaic power plants using images of the sky. This involves using imitation learning to train a neural network to approximate an optimal control policy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves control theory and optimization, which could place it in sub-categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
